[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "evidence_score": 0.9,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "evidence_reasons": [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "explicit_causal_language: likely related to",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "temporal_association: since starting medication",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "known_adr_match"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   ],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "detection_timestamp": "2026-03-04T18:33:12Z",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "status": "pending_review"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Sample aggregation signal:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```json
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "rxnorm_code": "329526",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "drug_name": "amlodipine 10mg oral tablet",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "event_term": "orthostatic hypotension",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "unique_patients": 14,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "total_mentions": 22,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "expected_rate": 4.2,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "observed_to_expected_ratio": 3.33,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "time_window_days": 30,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   "signal_status": "investigation_required"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Performance benchmarks:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Metric | Typical Value |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |--------|---------------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | End-to-end latency (per note) | 3-8 seconds |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Entity extraction precision | 88-94% (medications), 82-90% (conditions) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Adverse event relation detection precision | 70-85% |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Adverse event relation detection recall | 55-70% |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | False positive rate (after all filtering) | 15-30% of flagged events are not true AEs |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Cost per note (Comprehend Medical) | $0.20-0.50 (depends on note length) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Throughput | ~100-200 notes/minute (Lambda concurrency dependent) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Where it struggles:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Implicit adverse events with no causal language ("started having headaches" with medication mentioned paragraphs earlier)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Expected side effects generating noise (nausea in chemo patients, constipation in opioid patients)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Novel adverse reactions not in the knowledge base (these are the most valuable signals and the hardest to detect)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Very short notes with insufficient context for temporal reasoning
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Copy-pasted note sections that repeat mentions across visits without new clinical information
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## The Honest Take
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's what actually happens when you deploy adverse event detection in a health system.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The first week, the safety team is drowning. Every note that mentions a symptom near a medication gets flagged. Expected side effects dominate the output. Your pharmacovigilance team, who previously reviewed maybe 20 voluntary reports a month, is now looking at 500 automated detections a week. Most are noise.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The fix is iterative tuning of the expected-effects filter. You need a comprehensive "known and expected" database that you maintain by drug class. Statins cause myalgia. SSRIs cause GI upset. Beta-blockers cause fatigue. None of these are novel safety signals. Filter them out of the alert stream (but keep them in the database for aggregation, because a higher-than-expected rate of a "known" effect can still be a signal).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The hardest false negatives to address are the implicit mentions. "Patient feels worse since last visit" is potentially an adverse event if a new medication was started at the last visit. But connecting "feels worse" to a specific drug requires reasoning across notes, not just within a single note. Cross-note reasoning is architecturally expensive and introduces complexity that most first-generation systems skip. Plan for it in your roadmap but don't try to build it first.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The aggregation step is where the real value emerges, and it takes months. You need a critical mass of processed notes before disproportionality analysis becomes meaningful. In a health system processing 10,000 notes per day, you'll start seeing reliable signals after 2-3 months of operation. Smaller systems need longer. This means your stakeholders need patience, which is not a technology problem but is absolutely a deployment challenge.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m One thing that surprised me: the highest-value outputs weren't the individual high-severity alerts (those tend to be caught anyway through existing clinical workflows). The highest value was in moderate-severity events that individually seemed unremarkable but in aggregate revealed a real pattern. Fourteen patients with mild dizziness on the same medication formulation, from the same manufacturer, dispensed in the same quarter. That's a signal that no voluntary reporting system would ever surface.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Variations and Extensions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Integration with medication reconciliation.** Cross-reference detected adverse events with the patient's current medication list from the pharmacy system. This adds a validation layer: if the system detects a relationship between a drug and a symptom, but the pharmacy system shows the patient hasn't actually filled that prescription in six months, that's likely a false positive from a historical mention. The medication list becomes a plausibility check.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Vaccine adverse event detection.** The same architecture applies to vaccine safety surveillance (VAERS-equivalent at the institutional level). Vaccines have different temporal patterns than chronic medications (most reactions occur within 7-14 days of administration), and the knowledge base of expected vs. unexpected reactions is well-defined by the CDC. Narrower scope makes this a good pilot use case for the broader adverse event detection system.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Integration with patient-reported outcomes.** Extend the input beyond clinician-authored notes to include patient-reported data: patient portal messages, symptom questionnaires, and nurse triage call notes. Patient-reported symptoms often appear earlier and with more detail than what makes it into the formal clinical note. This catches the signal closer to onset.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Related Recipes
